 To carry out this process, it will be enough with: 

00:00:25.760 --> 00:00:28.960
 a computer, a USB cable and your BQ smartphone. 

00:00:28.960 --> 00:00:33.390
 Before starting the installation, you will need to download the necessary tools. 

00:00:33.390 --> 00:00:38.000
 Go to the mibqyyo.com website and click on the "Downloads" tab 

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:42.460
 It would only be to locate the model of your device and the chosen version and proceed to download 

00:00:42.460 --> 00:00:44.210
 the compressed file 

00:00:44.210 --> 00:00:47.940
 Remember to download the corresponding firmware version, in addition to the "Drivers" package 

00:00:47.940 --> 00:00:49.800
 and utilities. " 

00:00:53.890 --> 00:00:58.399
 Once all the elements have been downloaded, go to the folder where you saved the file 

00:00:58.399 --> 00:01:04.110
 "ADB Qualcomm.rar Drivers" you have downloaded. Double click and a box will open 

00:01:04.110 --> 00:01:06.180
 dialog to unzip the content. 

00:01:06.180 --> 00:01:10.810
 Press the "Extract" button and the program will ask you where you want to place the files. 

00:01:10.810 --> 00:01:14.620
 Tap "OK" and the decompression process will begin. 

00:01:14.620 --> 00:01:19.620
 After this step, a folder with two files will appear inside it 

00:01:19.620 --> 00:01:24.510
 Run the BQ Handset USB Drivers.exe application and several windows will appear. 

00:01:24.510 --> 00:01:29.130
 Follow them until the process is complete. 

00:01:29.130 --> 00:01:32.380
 On your phone, activate the "USB debugging" mode in the 

00:01:32.380 --> 00:01:36.650
 "Development options". If this option does not appear, go to "Phone information" 

00:01:36.650 --> 00:01:40.900
 and press seven times on "Compilation number" 

00:01:45.900 --> 00:01:48.770
 Then, activate the installer mode. 

00:01:48.770 --> 00:01:51.500
 To do this, go to "Settings-storage" 

00:01:51.500 --> 00:01:56.900
 Click on the three points and a button called "USB connection to the computer" will appear 

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:01.100
 Choose it, access the menu and uncheck the "Multimedia device" option 

00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:02.900
 if it is activated. 

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:08.100
 If everything is correct, "USB debugging enabled" should appear in the notification bar 

00:02:08.200 --> 00:02:09.200
 and "Connected as installer" 

00:02:09.300 --> 00:02:12.260
 Connect your terminal on to the computer and leave it for a few minutes 

00:02:12.260 --> 00:02:15.330
 until you install all the drivers. 

00:02:15.330 --> 00:02:19.050
 When everything is correct, you will see that they appear 

00:02:19.050 --> 00:02:21.050
 in the administrator, among others, the following devices. 

00:02:21.920 --> 00:02:22.850
 During the process, the phone will ask you to accept the fingerprint. To continue, press OK 

00:02:23.820 --> 00:02:24.380
 Loading "and you will see a dialog box to select the firmware you want 

00:02:24.390 --> 00:02:25.300
 install on the phone. 

00:02:25.300 --> 00:02:29.890
 Go to the firmware folder previously unzipped, select the text file 

00:02:29.890 --> 00:02:32.090
 that it contains (MT6577_Android_scatter_emmc ") and press" Open ". 

00:02:32.090 --> 00:02:36.120
 In the drop-down menu, select "Frimware Upgrade" and click on "Download". 

00:02:36.120 --> 00:02:37.590
 Perform the hard reset 

00:02:37.590 --> 00:02:42.710
 Connect your phone off to the PC using the USB cable. The bq symbol will appear 

00:02:42.710 --> 00:02:44.030
 and the battery indicator. 

00:02:44.030 --> 00:02:47.510
 When it disappears, the process will begin. When finished, a window with 

00:02:47.510 --> 00:02:50.350
 a green circle and the word OK. 

00:02:50.350 --> 00:02:51.170
 Victoria Presentation 

00:02:51.170 --> 00:02:54.460
 After this step, you can now disconnect your phone and turn it on normally. 

00:02:55.120 --> 00:02:59.000
 Finally, it resets the factory settings to complete the terminal process. 

00:02:59.540 --> 00:03:03.580
 If when executing file 8196, the hard reset procedure does not start on its own, 

00:03:03.580 --> 00:03:05.380
 try to do the following: 

00:03:05.760 --> 00:03:11.460
 Make sure the drivers are installed. To do this, go to Device Manager 

00:03:11.980 --> 00:03:18.600
 and check that, by connecting the phone in Installer mode and, with active USB debugging, it is recognized. 

00:03:18.600 --> 00:03:24.550
 Change to the different USB ports of your PC. If it's a desktop computer, try 

00:03:24.550 --> 00:03:26.310
 connect it to the rear ports. 

00:03:26.540 --> 00:03:30.720
 Check that the phone has enough battery, at least 30%. 

00:03:31.240 --> 00:03:34.900
 Following these steps, your BQ Aquaris E5 4G will be as good as new. 

